{
  "type": "excalidraw",
  "version": 2,
  "source": "mcp-excalidraw-server",
  "elements": [
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46w8ya8o9n139p",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 20,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "qz-mcp-server — Full system architecture (draft, for you to complete)",
      "fontSize": 24,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xfg7aq1ylu8a",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 1320,
      "height": 300,
      "backgroundColor": "#f8f9fa",
      "strokeColor": "#adb5bd",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xngi484agc8o",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 95,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "①  Concepts: what is MCP / FastMCP",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xyba7p5blys",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 130,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "MCP = Model Context Protocol.  A way for an LLM (a \"host\") to call tools and read resources hosted by external programs (\"servers\").",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xqb8rlfn07q",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 150,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "Think of it as: \"a typed plug for giving Claude a new capability without putting that capability inside Claude\".",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46x7w5kumbdj8e",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 190,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "text": "Wire format",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xf3p349rk6q8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 210,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• JSON-RPC 2.0 (request/response messages with method + params + id)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xnzo41nfo3v",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 225,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• Transports: stdio, streamable-HTTP (what we use), websocket",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46x7dhnv7op5uv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 240,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• Protocol revision we use: 2025-11-25",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xzjoef1tf4pi",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 275,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "text": "Three primitives the spec defines",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xnno9e37uxv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 295,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• tools     — functions the LLM can call.    Used heavily by us (speak, listen, start_call, ...)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xkat7efyz3ha",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 310,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• resources — data the LLM can read.        We don't use any.",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46x21bbeosk2p5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 325,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "• prompts   — templates the LLM can fetch. We don't use any.",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xja63zsui16",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 345,
      "strokeColor": "#868e96",
      "text": "(TODO: add anything else you want to remember about MCP — e.g. sampling, progress notifications, elicitation)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46x0gqjkh07e6q",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 190,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "text": "FastMCP",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.030Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xw3sh4zkc2z",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 210,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "The Python helper inside the official `mcp` package (Anthropic's reference SDK).",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xjlw0i40xoq",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 225,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "You instantiate `FastMCP(name, host, port, ...)` and decorate Python functions with `@mcp.tool()`.",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xlp7jia6pk5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 240,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "It handles the JSON-RPC plumbing, the schema generation, the HTTP transport.",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46x8zex6i9fkyx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 270,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "Our config: stateless_http=True, json_response=True — the",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xmyp27l2gagf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 285,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "recommended setup for streamable-HTTP servers under 2025-11-25.",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xica0rs3eig",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 305,
      "strokeColor": "#868e96",
      "text": "(TODO: note here whether you want stateful sessions later)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xjfejo7foa8",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 410,
      "width": 1320,
      "height": 540,
      "backgroundColor": "#f8f9fa",
      "strokeColor": "#adb5bd",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mpdlf46xkf6ryr6hfu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 425,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "text": "②  Process topology and what crosses each boundary",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T05:00:06.031Z",
      "version": 1
    },
    {
